### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core, compiler, language-service

### Description

Uninvoked signals in control flow blocks aren't reported as potential issues. An extended diagnostic ([NG8109](https://angular.dev/extended-diagnostics/NG8109)) exists to report these if used in template interpolations, but not for control flow. 

I just reviewed some code that contained a decently hard to spot bug related to an `@if` condition never being met, as it was apparently negating a `signal` without invoking it. 

The code looked similar to this:

```html
<!-- app.component.html -->

<!-- This is wrong, since isArchived is a signal. Hard to spot! -->
@if (!isArchived) {
  <div>Some template</div>
}
```

```ts
// app.component.ts

class SomeComponent {
  public isArchived = signal(false);
}
```

In the above example, the template inside the `@if`-block would never be shown, even if the `isArchived` signal would have a value of `true`, since signals themselves are always truthy.

---

This seems to only be an issue for **negated** signals in `@if` or `@else-if`, as all other control flow elements have other diagnostics reported that would prevent compilation.

Given the following component:
```ts
import { Component, signal, input } from '@angular/core';
import { RouterOutlet } from '@angular/router';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
})
export class AppComponent {
  public show = signal(false);

  public otherBoolean = signal(false);

  public userPermissions = signal<'admin' | 'reviewer' | 'editor'>('admin');

  public arrayLike = input<string[]>([]);
}
```

Uninvoked signals in all blocks are reported by existing compiler errors (specifically, `NG4` and `NG8`). Only the negated uninvoked signal is not reported. 

<img width="1205" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0f74d9f4-55ab-452a-b2cf-f6148ea191fb" />

### Proposed solution

It would be nice to have reporting on either specifically _negated, uninvoked signals_, or any uninvoked signals in control flow syntax.

I can think of the following options:

**Extend NG8109 to report uninvoked signals in control flow**
It's a similar issue, since uninvoked signals are most likely developer errors that can lead to bugs. Unsure how this affects existing configurations, as this can lead to new errors being reported / suppressed. 

**Create a new extended diagnostic**
This would report on uninvoked signals in control flow syntax, as outlined in the description.


### Alternatives considered

- The existing [NG8109](https://angular.dev/extended-diagnostics/NG8109) diagnostic - This doesn't report for uninvoked signals in control flow syntax.
- Custom ESLint rule - Hard to implement, requires type information and parsing the control flow syntax.

